		<technology>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="en">A processing sequence similar to Salar de Atacama has been suggested. As a first step, the brine would be enriched from 0.07 wt.% Li to 4 wt.% Li in evaporation ponds. Quicklime would be added to the evaporation ponds. In the processing plant, purification steps would consist of B removal by organic solvent extraction, Mg and Ca removal by adding soda ash and quicklime. Then, Li2CO3 (technical grade) would precipitate by heating the pulp and adding soda ash. Li2CO3 (technical grade) would then be dissolved in water at low temperatures and re-heated to precipitate Li2CO3 (battery grade).</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="zh">有人建议采用与阿塔卡马盐湖类似的加工顺序。第一步，在蒸发池中将盐水的锂含量从 0.07 wt.% 提高到 4 wt.%。蒸发池中还将加入生石灰。在加工厂，净化步骤包括通过有机溶剂萃取去除硼，通过添加纯碱和生石灰去除镁和钙。然后，通过加热纸浆并加入纯碱，析出 Li2CO3（工业级）。然后，在低温下将 Li2CO3（工业级）溶解在水中，并再次加热以析出 Li2CO3（电池级）。</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">Battery-grade lithium carbonate produced through brine precipitation in Argentina's Salar del Hombre Muerto is primarily used in lithium-ion batteries, which are used in a wide range of portable electronic devices, electric vehicles and grid energy storage solutions.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">通过阿根廷死亡盐湖卤水沉淀法生产的电池级碳酸锂主要用于锂离子电池，这类电池广泛应用于便携式电子设备、电动汽车和电网储能解决方案中。</technologicalApplicability>
